title: Other Currency Outside the Treasury and Federal Reserve Banks for United States
notes:
Series Is Presented Here As Three Variables--(1)--Original Data, 1878-1914 (2)--Original Data, 1914-1919 (3)--Original Data, 1919-1949. Data Exclude Gold, Silver, And National Bank Notes, But Include Minor Coin. Data For Federal Reserve Banks Are Revised By The Federal Reserve Board. Beginning March 1915 Treasury Notes Of 1890 Are Excluded From "Other Currency" And Included In Silver. Source: Computed By NBER Using Data From The U.S. Treasury Department Data: Annual Reports Of The Treasurer, 1886 And Following Years; Circulation Statements Of U.S. Money, 1887 And Following Years.

This NBER data series m14136b appears on the NBER website in Chapter 14 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter14.html.

NBER Indicator: m14136b
